- The jaw force is the individual force applied by each of the two jaws of the gripper;
- The cumulative average grip force provides a running average of the grip force over the data records for each test;
- The maximum jaw force is the highest combined force applied by the two jaws during a specific configuration of the gripper;
- The configuration name and test description provide context for understanding the conditions under which the grip force was measured.

- "Strongest grip" refers to the highest average grip force;
- "Robotic grippers" are mechanical devices used to grasp and manipulate objects;
- "Average grip force" is the mean force measured over multiple tests for a specific gripper configuration.

